  "text": "where B is the set of all k × ℓ matrices such that one of the elements in each column takes one and others are all zero. This problem is again NP-hard so we may not be able to obtain the optimal solution. A relaxation approach is to allow A to take real values, i.e., A ∈ R k×ℓ . Then the solution of the relaxed problem is shown to agree with the solution of the Laplacian eigenmap [CITATION_1] . This implies that the embedded samples by the Laplacian eigenmap has 'soft' cluster structure.",
